  "sections": {
    "Background": {
      "text": "Most frequent and serious ocular opportunistic infection\nLeading cause of blindness in\nAIDS\npatients\nTypically occurs with CD4 less than 50",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": [
        {
          "text": "AIDS",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/AIDS"
        }
      ]
    },
    "Clinical_Features": {
      "text": "Variable, but may include:\nChange in visual acuity,\nvisual loss\nVisual field cuts\n(Scotomas, loss of central vision)\nFloaters\n, flashing lights\nPhotophobia\nFundoscopy\n:\nFluffy white perivascular lesions\nDirty white granular retinal necrosis\nAdjacent hemorrhage - \"Pizza pie\" appearance\nEye pain\n/\nredness",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": [
